{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ce269171-37d4-46ec-af60-276f9021d2c7","content":"## What Happened\n\nApple's security frameworks (`Security.framework` / `CommonCrypto`) **dropped DSA support**. .NET on macOS delegates to the native crypto libraries, so once Apple removed it, `DSA.Create()` throws **`PlatformNotSupportedException`** on macOS. This breaking change has been progressing through .NET versions (first flagged around .NET 7).\n\nYour .NET 10 builds may have only been tested on Linux/Windows, or used a code path that deferred the `DSA.Create()` call. With .NET 11 the platform check is strict — it fails immediately.\n\n## How to Fix It\n\nSince you only need to **verify** legacy signatures (not generate new ones), you have two practical options:\n\n### Option 1 — Use BouncyCastle (recommended, cross-platform managed crypto)\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography\n```\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\npublic static bool VerifyDsaSignature(\n    byte[] message, byte[] signature, DsaPublicKeyParameters publicKey)\n{\n    var verifier = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA256withDSA\");\n    verifier.Init(forSigning: false, publicKey);\n    verifier.BlockUpdate(message, 0, message.Length);\n    return verifier.VerifySignature(signature);\n}\n```\n\nThis is a fully managed implementation — no native dependencies, works identically on Linux, Windows, and macOS.\n\n### Option 2 — Platform-switch with OpenSSL on macOS\n\nInstall OpenSSL on macOS (`brew install openssl`) and use P/Invoke, but this adds deployment complexity and is fragile. **Not recommended.**\n\n## Long-Term Recommendation\n\nDSA is considered **legacy and deprecated** across the industry (NIST FIPS 186-5 dropped DSA for new signatures). Plan a migration to **ECDSA** or **Ed25519**, which are supported natively on all .NET platforms.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b49e6663-7e00-4112-a011-b604a4180419","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET compatibility issue with DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) on macOS after upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11. Let me think about what I know about this topic.\n\nThis is a well-known breaking change in .NET. Starting with .NET 7, Microsoft began deprecating older cryptographic algorithms, and DSA specifically has been affected on macOS.\n\nLet me recall the details:\n\nIn .NET 7, Microsoft made a breaking change where DSA.Create() throws a PlatformNotSupportedException on macOS. This is because Apple's Security framework (and CommonCrypto/CryptoKit) dropped support for DSA. On Linux, DSA works through OpenSSL, and on Windows it works through CNG/CAPI.\n\n\nI need to reconsider the timeline here. The user mentions upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11, and given we're in May 2026, that would mean .NET 10 is the current release and .NET 11 is in preview. But the DSA breaking change on macOS happened much earlier, around .NET 7. If the user says it works on .NET 10 and breaks on .NET 11, that's unusual since the issue should have already manifested in earlier versions. Let me think about whether there's a new change in .NET 11 or if the user might be describing a different scenario. The real issue is that Apple removed DSA from their security frameworks, so .NET on macOS can't access it anymore—this breaking change came in .NET 7. To work around it, I could use a managed DSA implementation if I only need to verify signatures, or pull in a library like BouncyCastle, or manually parse DSA parameters using the ASN.1 package and delegate to a third-party crypto library. The core issue is that macOS doesn't support DSA through Apple's native security framework, so .NET throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` when calling `DSA.Create()` on that platform. This breaking change has been rolling out across .NET versions, and the fix involves either switching to ECDSA/EdDSA or using a managed cryptography library that doesn't depend on platform-specific implementations.","outputTokens":1804,"requestId":"C440:298C73:1EE02D3:22B57EF:6A07C980"},"id":"bc54c1d2-f5fe-4458-87a2-1591924e7700","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:34:27.070Z","parentId":"1b1bcf96-0f39-489f-89e8-9dfb79ea2292"}
